From: OpenWRT Developer
Subject: [PATCH] mac80211: sta_info: fix UAF race in power save delivery

The 'ps_lock' spinlock in 'sta_info' can be accessed after the station
has been partially torn down, leading to a "spinlock bad magic" BUG.
This happens because 'ieee80211_sta_ps_deliver_wakeup' can be called
asynchronously while the station is being removed.

Fix this by:
1. Checking 'WLAN_STA_INSERTED' flag before touching the lock.
2. Ensure 'sdata' is valid.
3. Adding a memory barrier to ensure flags are read correctly.

Signed-off-by: OpenWRT Developer
---
--- a/net/mac80211/sta_info.c
+++ b/net/mac80211/sta_info.c
@@ -107,6 +107,11 @@ void ieee80211_purge_sta_txqs(struct sta_info *sta)
 	struct ieee80211_local *local = sta->sdata->local;
 	int i;
 
+	if (!sta->uploaded || !sta->sdata)
+		return;
+	/* Ensure flags are visible before proceeding */
+	smp_rmb();
+
 	if (sta->sta.txq[0]) {
 		for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(sta->sta.txq); i++) {
 			struct txq_info *txqi;
@@ -126,6 +131,10 @@ static void __cleanup_single_sta(struct sta_info *sta)
 	struct ieee80211_local *local = sdata->local;
 	struct ps_data *ps;
 
+	if (!test_sta_flag(sta, WLAN_STA_INSERTED))
+		return;
+	smp_rmb();
+
 	if (test_sta_flag(sta, WLAN_STA_PS_STA) ||
 	    test_sta_flag(sta, WLAN_STA_PS_DRIVER) ||
 	    test_sta_flag(sta, WLAN_STA_PS_DELIVER)) {
@@ -1783,6 +1783,14 @@
 	unsigned long flags;
 	struct ps_data *ps;
 
+	/*
+	 * CRITICAL: Race condition check.
+	 * If station is not inserted, do not touch spinlocks to prevent UAF.
+	 */
+	if (!sta || !sta->sdata || !test_sta_flag(sta, WLAN_STA_INSERTED))
+		return;
+	smp_rmb(); /* Ensure flag read is visible */
+
 	if (sdata->vif.type == NL80211_IFTYPE_AP_VLAN)
 		sdata = container_of(sdata->bss, struct ieee80211_sub_if_data,
 				     u.ap);
